<p><a name="Education_and_Background" id="Education_and_Background"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Richard_Bandler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Education and Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Education and Background</span></h2>
<p>Bandler holds a BA (1973) in <a href="/wiki/Philosophy" title="Philosophy">Philosophy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Psychology" title="Psychology">Psychology</a> from the University of California, Santa Cruz (UCSC)<a href="http://www.geocities.com/bandlertrial/bandler3.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.geocities.com/bandlertrial/bandler3.html" rel="nofollow">[1]</a> and an MA (1975) in <a href="/wiki/Psychology" title="Psychology">Psychology</a> from Lone Mountain College in San Francisco.</p>
<p><a name="Neuro-linguistic_programming" id="Neuro-linguistic_programming"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Richard_Bandler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Neuro-linguistic programming">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Neuro-linguistic programming</span></h2>
<div style="float:right;margin:0px 0px 15px 20px;padding-left:10px;background-color:#fff;">
